name: Air Fryer Tilapia Milanese for Two
author: Soup Loving Nicole
summary: Crispy lemon flavored tilapia made easy in the air fryer.
directions: Preheat the air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) according to manufacturer's instructions
Pat tilapia fillets dry using a paper towel
Coat both sides of fish with flour
Whisk egg, lemon juice, and salt together in a shallow bowl
Place bread crumbs and lemon-pepper seasoning in a separate shallow bowl
Dip flour-coated fish first in egg and then in bread crumb mixture
Press down on the fish so that the bread crumbs stick
Spray both sides of fish with cooking spray
Place fillets in the air fryer basket and cook for 5 minutes
Flip fish over using a spatula and cook for 3 minutes more
